adj. 1. Resembling or functioning as a foot: pedate appendages. 2. (Zoology) Having feet: pedate larvae. 3. (Botany) Having palmately divided lobes with the lateral loves cleft or divided: a pedate leaf. [Latin pedatus, past participle of pedare, to furnush with feet, from pes, ped-, foot. See ped- in indo-european index somewhere.] (From American Heritage 2005 ed.)